---
alwaysApply: true
---

* Authentication must be wallet-based (no username/password).
* Use message signing instead of storing sensitive data on-chain.
* Smart contract should only handle verification logic, not store unnecessary user data.
* Backend (Node.js/Express) should verify signatures using ethers.js.
* Frontend should use MetaMask or WalletConnect.
* Use JWT only AFTER wallet verification (hybrid auth).
* Ensure replay attack protection using nonce system.
* Smart contract must include:

  * Ownership control (Ownable)
  * Event logging for login attempts
* Do not store private data on blockchain.
* Gas usage should be minimized.
* Include test cases using Hardhat or Foundry.
